We're having a CITI CAFE fundraiser Friday, Feruary 3rd from 2-7:30. Please drop by and support the team. We really need money because robots are expensive and we are going to an important competition. Please put your receipts in the jar. Do tell your friends and family. Thanks, thanks, much appreciate. https://www.facebook.com/events/263113604123409/

New season, new team photo!

Our November competition was postponed to later date so Team Athena competed for our first time this season today!! Throughout Thanksgiving break, the team met up multiple times to add new parts and fix minor problems with driving. The robot now drives very smoothly and is able to successfully get balls in and out of its shooting mechanism. It was exciting to present our robot to the world! FTC 9657 Athena Robotics updated their cover photo.

Robotics = <3
Come play with metal, saws, and electricity! All while not wearing protective gear!
Really though, be safe, wear protective gear no matter how uncomfortable.
Do it.

Athena Robotics is the proud recipient of the $1,000 grant from The Dow Chemical Company's  #ShapeTheFuture contest! We are so grateful to everyone who has voted and supported us, we couldn't have done it without you. This is an incredible opportunity given to us by DOW, especially since we are a first year team. We thank you all so much and look forward to an awesome season! We can't wait to put the money to good use, making an incredible robot for the next build season!

Good job to all our members, but especially Greta  and Kaitlyn who put a lot of effort in making the video! FTC 9657 Athena Robotics is with Kaitlyn Gunadhi and 9 others.

Hi everyone,

We would be extremly grateful if you took a few seconds out of your time everyday to vote for FTC 9657: Team Athena on DOW365's #ShapeTheFuture contest! The contest runs on votes so we would greatly appreciate it if you would vote and share this to as many people as you know.

VOTING ENDS APRIL 24!
So please vote EVERY 24 HOURS!

For the contest we worked hard to come up with the idea of the Micro Whale and bring the video to life!

With the money from the grant, Athena Robotics would buy materials needed for the build season. In the past build season there were many designs and ides that we could not see through because we did not have adequate funding. We would not like this issue to prevent us from building a successful robot in the future. We would also use our funds for outreaches.

We thank DOW365 for giving us this opportunity!
Happy birthday to our mentor Bhudeb Mukhopadhyay! FTC 9657 Athena Robotics is with Kaitlyn Gunadhi and 4 others.
